    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-12-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1470"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1470">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/2173.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of War</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 13, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>While the Department has learned with interest of the decision of the Supreme
                    Court of the Canal Zone in refusing a writ of habeas corpus applied for by
                    General Luis Mena the Nicaraguan revolutionary leader, it is inclined to believe
                    that Mena is no longer dangerous to the peace of Nicaragua. I therefore
                    recommend that instructions be telegraphed to the Canal Zone authorities to
                    permit Mena and his son to depart if they wish to do so.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
